      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "OAK PARK MADDISON (3) got off the mark in great style two back at Oakbank and then followed it up with a strong chasing effort in town, only beaten 2L in a blanket finish. Has been kept on the fresh side with 27 days in-between and reunites with winning hoop. Looks the one. ANOTHER BRIDE (4) also impressed in her maiden two back when leading pillar-to-post here. Went close to making it two on the bounce last time and has since been freshened with 58 days. Have to take seriously. BENIGN (2) has also had 58 days between runs, after arriving just in time here on December 31. Keeps the 2kg claimer on and draws well again. In the mix. UNCLOTHED (7) backs up quickly after a forgettable first-up run. Can only go up.",
